 Idea inks $500m deal

 Mumbai, May 17 (PTI): The AVB group company Idea Cellular today inked a $500-million two-year deal with telecom equipment maker Nokia Siemens Network to expand its GSM service.

 Nokia Siemens Network will help Idea deploy its network technologies in Delhi, Haryana, Uttar Pradesh (east), Uttar Pradesh (west), Andhra Pradesh and Kerala, Idea managing director Sanjeev Aga said.

 The contract also includes supply of value-added services. The $500million programme is part of Ideas Rs 9,000crore capital expenditure plan for two years, Aga said.

 Idea has got licences to operate in Mumbai and Bihar, but is awaiting spectrum allocation. 




